src:
Stolen car found wedged in bushes, police say
04 Nov 2019, 19:00 by Logan Rude
MADISON, Wis. - Police said they found a stolen car wedged in some bushes on Kottke Drive on Sunday morning.
The owner of the vehicle said her car was stolen Friday morning after she left the car unlocked and running while she waited for it to warm up, according to an incident report.
The car was found with front-end damage, police said. According to the report, police found a purse, two sets of keys and three garage door openers, none of which belonged to the owner of the car.
